# Rocket.new — Cursor Behavior Rules

> CRITICAL RULES AT TOP AND BOTTOM OF THIS FILE.
> These govern HOW Cursor operates — read before touching any code.

---

## PROJECT IDENTITY

You are working on a **Rocket.new-generated web application** — a full-stack Next.js app with a specific, fixed tech stack. Your job is to fix bugs and implement features by writing code. Stay consistent with the conventions Rocket generates.

**Fixed stack — cannot change after project creation:**
- **Framework**: Next.js (TypeScript) App Router — OR — React (JavaScript) Vite
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS (`darkMode: 'class'` always)
- **Backend**: Supabase via `@supabase/ssr` (the SSR package — NOT deprecated `auth-helpers-nextjs`)
- **Deployment**: Netlify
- **Payments**: Stripe (if present)

