## HARD FORBIDDEN PATTERNS — NEVER VIOLATE

### ❌ 1. NEVER `getSession()` in server-side code
```typescript
// ❌ FORBIDDEN — does not validate JWT, can be spoofed
const { data: { session } } = await supabase.auth.getSession()

// ✅ ALWAYS — validates JWT with Supabase Auth server
const { data: { user }, error } = await supabase.auth.getUser()
if (error || !user) redirect('/login')
```

### ❌ 1b. getClaims() in middleware, getUser() for sensitive operations
```typescript
// Middleware runs on EVERY request — use getClaims() (local validation, microseconds)
const { data: claims } = await supabase.auth.getClaims()
// claims.sub = user ID, claims.user_role = custom claim

// API routes processing payments/data — use getUser() (server validation, ~100ms)
const { data: { user } } = await supabase.auth.getUser()
// Validates with Supabase server — catches revoked tokens
```

### ❌ 2. NEVER `request.json()` in Stripe webhook handlers
```typescript
// ❌ FORBIDDEN — destroys raw bytes, signature fails silently
const body = await request.json()

// ✅ ALWAYS — raw text preserves bytes for HMAC verification
const body = await request.text()
const event = stripe.webhooks.constructEvent(body, sig, process.env.STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET!)
```

### ❌ 3. NEVER browser Supabase client in Server Components
```typescript
// ❌ FORBIDDEN — browser client cannot read server-side cookies
import { createClient } from '@/lib/supabase/client'  // in a Server Component

// ✅ CORRECT — server client reads cookies via next/headers
import { createClient } from '@/lib/supabase/server'
```

### ❌ 4. NEVER `middleware.ts` inside `/app`
```
app/middleware.ts    ❌ — Next.js ignores this completely
middleware.ts        ✅ — project root
src/middleware.ts    ✅ — if using src/ directory
```

### ❌ 5. NEVER skip awaiting `cookies()` or `headers()` in Next.js 15
```typescript
// ❌ Next.js 14 syntax — breaks in Next.js 15
const cookieStore = cookies()

// ✅ Next.js 15
const cookieStore = await cookies()
const headersList = await headers()
```

### ❌ 6. NEVER expose service role key to the browser
```typescript
// ❌ FORBIDDEN — full database bypass exposed to anyone
process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY

// ✅ Server-only — never NEXT_PUBLIC_ prefix
process.env.SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY
```

### ❌ 7. NEVER use deprecated Supabase packages
```typescript
// ❌ FORBIDDEN — deprecated, causes auth SSR bugs
import { createServerComponentClient } from '@supabase/auth-helpers-nextjs'
import { createClientComponentClient } from '@supabase/auth-helpers-nextjs'

// ✅ Use @supabase/ssr
import { createBrowserClient } from '@supabase/ssr'   // browser
import { createServerClient } from '@supabase/ssr'    // server
```

### ❌ New projects use sb_publishable_ / sb_secret_ keys (not anon / service_role)
```typescript
// Projects created after November 2025 use NEW key names:
// NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY  (was: NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY)
// SUPABASE_SECRET_KEY                   (was: SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY)
// Edge Functions: SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY (was: SUPABASE_ANON_KEY)

// sb_publishable_ is NOT a JWT — never use as Authorization: Bearer token
// supabase-js handles headers automatically — only relevant for raw fetch() calls

// Safe pattern — works with BOTH legacy and new projects:
const key = process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY
         ?? process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY!
```
When working on a project, check Dashboard → Settings → API to confirm key format.

### ❌ 8. NEVER produce diffs containing `// ... existing code ...`
```typescript
// ❌ FORBIDDEN — this silently deletes the code it replaces
function example() {
  // ... existing code ...  ← THIS DELETES REAL CODE
  newLogic()
}

// ✅ ALWAYS — show the complete file content or exact line changes
// Never use ellipsis placeholders in diffs
```
**Why**: Cursor has a confirmed bug (March 2026) called "Lazy Delete" where it replaces
large code blocks with `// ... existing code ...`. If accepted, that code is permanently deleted.


