## TECH STACK CONVENTIONS

### Supabase Client — Which File to Use
| Context | Import From |
|---|---|
| `'use client'` component | `@/lib/supabase/client.ts` |
| Server Component | `@/lib/supabase/server.ts` |
| Route Handler (`route.ts`) | `@/lib/supabase/server.ts` |
| Server Action (`'use server'`) | `@/lib/supabase/server.ts` |
| `middleware.ts` | `@/lib/supabase/middleware.ts` → `updateSession()` |

### Next.js App Router Conventions
- API routes: `app/api/[name]/route.ts` — exports named `GET`, `POST`, `PUT`, `DELETE`
- Server Actions: `'use server'` directive at top of function or file
- Dynamic routes: `app/users/[id]/page.tsx`
- Protected routes: server-side `getUser()` + `redirect('/login')` if null — never client-side only
- Loading states: `app/[route]/loading.tsx` — auto-shown by Next.js
- Error boundaries: `app/[route]/error.tsx` — must be `'use client'`
- Default to Server Components — `'use client'` only when hooks/events/browser APIs are needed

### Supabase Conventions
- RLS enabled on every table — no exceptions
- Use `auth.uid()` in all RLS policies
- Use `.maybeSingle()` when row may not exist, `.single()` only when guaranteed
- Profile trigger: `on_auth_user_created` auto-creates a row in `profiles` table on signup
- Migration SQL lives in `supabase/migrations/` folder
- Edge Functions live in `supabase/functions/` folder

