## TOKEN EFFICIENCY RULES

These rules reduce cost and improve response quality simultaneously.

### 1. MCP before files
Query live database state via MCP before reading any local files.
A schema query via MCP = ~150 tokens. Reading a migration file = ~2,000 tokens.

### 2. Precise file references over @codebase
`@specific-file.ts` over `@codebase` for known locations.
`@codebase` triggers full semantic search — expensive. Use only for discovery.

### 3. Session length awareness
After 10 exchanges: offer /fresh-session.
Long history = noise + cost. A fresh session with summary = better answers cheaper.

### 4. Model budget discipline
`cursor-composer` for 90% of tasks. Never escalate to Opus by default.
Escalate only when genuinely needed — the task definition determines the model, not habit.

### 5. Notepads over re-typing
Any template you type twice → make it a Notepad.
Reference with /use-notepad instead of re-typing every session.

