## ⚠️ ISR SESSION LEAK — CRITICAL SECURITY RULE

NEVER use ISR (revalidate) or route-level caching on authenticated pages or layouts.
Supabase session cookies in cached responses can be served to different users.

```typescript
// FORBIDDEN on any page/layout that uses auth:
export const revalidate = 60          // ❌ can serve User A's session to User B

// REQUIRED on all protected pages/layouts:
export const dynamic = 'force-dynamic' // ✅ always fresh, never cached
```

