## ⚠️ CRITICAL RULES — REPEATED AT BOTTOM (HIGH ATTENTION ZONE)

1. `getUser()` not `getSession()` — always in server code
2. `request.text()` not `request.json()` — always in Stripe webhooks
3. `lib/supabase/server.ts` in Server Components — `lib/supabase/client.ts` in `'use client'` only
4. `middleware.ts` at project root — never inside `/app`
5. `await cookies()` — required in Next.js 15, not optional
6. Never `NEXT_PUBLIC_` on service role key
7. Never `@supabase/auth-helpers-nextjs` — use `@supabase/ssr`
8. Explain before applying — state changes before making them
9. One file at a time — never multi-file sweeps
10. Minimal scope — fix what was asked, nothing more
